   <pb facs="6"/>
   <head>THE AVTHOR TO the Reader.</head>
   <lg>
      <l>Let euerie man, if he be wife,</l>
      <l>Though he be not exprest by name.</l>
      <l>With indgement deep, and good aduise,</l>
      <l>Mark wel this Glasse: for in the same</l>
      <l>A perfect picture painted is,</l>
      <l>Of euerlasting bale or blis.</l>
      <l>Most sure we are, that we must die,</l>
      <l>But when, or how, God only knowes:</l>
      <l>O ten times happie then, say I,</l>
      <l>Is he that well his time best owes:</l>
      <l>But wo to him ten thousand fold,</l>
      <l>Whō death as prisoner fast doth hold.</l>
   </lg>
</div>
